cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically object pose estimation using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotic grasping tests, which suggests it could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). The use of neural networks for object pose estimation suggests it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves the use of motion capture systems, which could suggest it falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of 3D convolutions, which could suggest it falls under cs.GR (Graphics).
